# P3-008: plink_clump — LD Clumping of Association Results

## Goal

Implement `plink_clump(path)` — a DuckDB table function that performs LD-based
clumping of association test results, equivalent to plink2's `--clump`. Groups
significant variants into LD-defined loci around index (lead) variants.

## Prerequisites

- P2-001 merged (shared infrastructure in `plink_common.hpp/cpp`)
- P2-004 merged (plink_ld — LD computation infrastructure)
- P2-006 or external p-values (clumping operates on pre-computed p-values)

## Depends On

P2-004 (LD computation). Clumping requires computing r² between variant pairs,
reusing the same `PgrGet()` + correlation math from plink_ld.

## Branch

`feature/P3-008-plink-clump`

## Priority

**Medium-high.** Clumping is one of the most common post-GWAS steps. It
identifies independent association signals by grouping significant variants
that are in LD with an index SNP. Essential for downstream analyses:
fine-mapping, pathway analysis, PRS construction.

